Steps to install SASS:

1. Ensure you have Node.js installed on your system
2. Install SASS globally using npm:
   npm install -g sass
3. Verify installation by checking version:
   sass --version
4. SASS is now ready to use for compiling .scss files

Alternative installation methods:
- Using Homebrew (macOS): brew install sass/sass/sass
- Using standalone package from official SASS website
- Using specific version: npm install -g sass@1.77.8

Note: SASS was successfully installed globally and is available system-wide.
